# Kimodo text-to-motion (3DAIGC-API / DGX)

Read **`memory-bank/kimodo-text-to-motion-ops.md`** at task start when Kimodo, text-to-motion, or animation job failures are mentioned.

## Agent must execute (not delegate)

On Kimodo failure or setup — **same global rule as all tasks** (see `agent-run-instructions.mdc`):

1. `grep` / `tail logs/scheduler.log` for job id, worker load, traceback
2. `curl` job history + submit test job if verifying fix
3. `bash scripts/prefetch_kimodo_deps.sh` if Llama cache incomplete
4. `bash scripts/restart_services.sh` after config changes
5. Verify 4 Llama shards: `model-00001-of-00004` … `model-00004-of-00004`

**Do not** reply with "run this script" — execute it (global rule: `agent-run-instructions.mdc`).

## Invariants (do not revert)

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| `worker_load_timeout_sec` | `3600` in `config/models.yaml` for `kimodo_text_to_motion` |
| `TEXT_ENCODER_DEVICE` | `cpu` in `.env` |
| Prefetch script | `scripts/prefetch_kimodo_deps.sh` |

Default scheduler worker load timeout is **900s** — insufficient for first Llama download.

## Normal log lines

- `Text encoder service is unreachable, falling back to local LLM2Vec encoder` — expected (no sidecar)
- `Waiting up to 3600s for worker … model load` — expected on cold start

## Frontend counterpart

OpenNexus3DStudio: `KimodoMotionPromptBar.jsx`, `taskManager.js` text-to-motion flow. Backend-only changes sync via `OpenNexus3DStudio/scripts/sync-to-pc.sh --include-agent-context` when rules/memory-bank updated on DGX.
